import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['precipitation'].plot(kind='hist', bins=30, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Precipitation (inches)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation in Seattle from 2012 to 2015?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['temp_max'], color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['temp_max'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Maximum Temperature (F)')
    plt.title('How does the maximum temperature vary throughout the year in Seattle?')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['wind'], data['temp_max'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Wind Speed (mph)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Maximum Temperature (F)')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between wind speed and temperature in Seattle?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['weather'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'green', 'red', 'orange', 'purple'])
    plt.title('What is the most common weather condition observed in Seattle from 2012 to 2015?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Weather Condition')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))

    ax.axhline(y=data['temp_min'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean Minimum Temperature')
    ax.legend()
    ax.set_xlabel('Precipitation (inches)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Minimum Temperature (F)')
    ax.set_title('How does precipitation affect the minimum temperature in Seattle?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
